class Solution {
    public int countKDifference(int[] nums, int k) {
        int[] count = new int[101];
        int result = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            if (num - k >= 1) result += count[num - k];
            if (num + k <= 100) result += count[num + k];
            count[num]++;
        }
        return result;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Utilizes a frequency count array to track occurrences of numbers, allowing for a single pass through the input array to count pairs with the specified absolute difference.
